*Introducing Reverse Pickups*


Introducing *Reverse Pickup Capability* with structured handling for
both *Failed
Pickups* and *Partial Pickups*.

Until now there was no native system capability to create, manage, or
govern reverse pickup flows, including scenarios where pickups fail or are
only partially completed.

What=E2=80=99s New


Reverse Pickup


Returns and reverse fulfilment are now fundamental to commerce
operations. Reverse
movement type is now fully supported within the system.


This enables:

   -

   Creation of reverse orders
   -

   Handle real-world pickup outcomes
   -

   Capture structured exception data
   -

   Enforce validation where required
   -

   Maintain operational visibility


This release establishes reverse pickup as a first-class capability, built
for scale and control.
Failed & Partial Pickup Capability


Reverse pickups also support two structured outcomes:


*Failed Pickup*

   -

   Configure custom failed pickup reasons
   -

   Define required proof type (OTP or Call verification)
   -

   Maintain validated exception records


*Partial Pickup*

   -

   Adjust item quantities during pickup
   -

   Select a mandatory reason for partial collection
   -

   Clearly record picked vs not-picked items


Both capabilities are independently configurable to ensure clarity between
complete failures and partial collections.
Reverse Pickup Handling in the Rider App


Reverse pickups are now fully supported within the Rider App, including
clear handling for both *Failed* and *Partial *outcomes.


*Failed Pickup*

   -

   Mark the pickup as failed
   -

   Select a defined reason
   -

   Complete required OTP/Call verification
   -

   Submit with validated proof


*Partial Pickup*

   -

   Adjust item quantities during pickup
   -

   Select a reason for partial collection
   -

   Review picked vs. not-picked items


This ensures reverse outcomes are clearly recorded, validated, and visible.
What This Means For You

   -

   Reverse pickups can now be created and managed within the product
   -

   Failed and Partial Pickup scenarios are supported natively
   -

   Validation can be enforced for better accountability
   -

   Reverse logistics workflows are now scalable and governed


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned!!
